      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TARAWI MIKE (4) is a smart dog who pinged the lids and cleared the pack early, leading throughout to win (22.52) at this track in Grade 5/6 over 400m. Hard to go past form here, unbeaten in two starts. Winner at his latest appearance in the quickest time on the card. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. XENI BALE (1) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fifth (35.24) in a Grade 5 at Cannington. Has a good record at this journey. The form out of last race has been strong. Better than last start and can bounce back. TIME HAS COME (2) has a strong record this track and trip with three wins and three placings from nine starts. Comes off a (22.77) win last time, scoring by one length in a Grade 5 over 400m at this track. Looks well placed here and among the chances. AMITY ISLAND (3) won in slick time last start. Big chance on that form.",
